    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>A Tough Cow to Follow</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <byline class="print_byline">By ELAINE LOUIE</byline>
      <byline class="normalized_byline">Louie, Elaine</byline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Chicago plans to install hundreds of artists' conceptions of fiberglass furniture around city next summer; photo (Currents column) (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>Last year, 324 decorated fiberglass cows brought $250 million in tourism to Chicago, said Michael Lash, a director in the city's Cultural Affairs Department. Next summer comes Suite Home Chicago, with artists' conceptions of fiberglass sofas, chairs with ottomans, and television consoles, right -- all boxy, so water will run off, and reinforced with steel, because people will sit on them. ''The furniture is 1950's Moderne that recalled people's memories,'' said Nathan Mason, a curator of special projects. Sponsors pay $4,000 (a television) to $10,000 (a suite). Information, (312) 742-5595.</p>
        <p>ELAINE LOUIE</p>
      </block>
